title gitleaks: recommended, not required
edge explains commit:22675e2f03935d72f35759a3bcd7da1ffbebba75

gitleaks is strongly recommended but not a strict dependency.

Three scan layers, all skip gracefully when gitleaks is absent:
1. Inline (mycelium.sh note): gitleaks dir on tmpfile before write
2. Pre-commit hook: gitleaks git --staged
3. Pre-push hook: gitleaks git (--all default, covers refs/notes/*)

Key findings:
- gitleaks v8.30 scans notes by default (git log --all includes refs/notes/*)
- gitleaks stdin mode does NOT load rules — use dir mode with tmpfile instead
- git notes remove does NOT erase history — the add commit persists in --all
- test suite: test-gitleaks.sh, 16 tests, runs independently, SKIPs without gitleaks
